  "prompt": "Can Windex leach through aquarium glass?",
  "response": "No, Windex cannot leach through aquarium glass. Glass is an impermeable material, meaning that cleaning products like Windex cannot penetrate or leach through it. However, it's important to be cautious when using Windex or other cleaning products near an aquarium, as the chemicals could potentially harm the aquatic life if they come into contact with the water. Always ensure that cleaning products do not enter the aquarium and consider wiping the glass with a damp cloth to avoid any risk of contamination.",
